  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "How can I delete iPhone battery usage stats?",
  "response": "To delete the battery usage statistics on your iPhone, you can reset the Battery Stats, but it's important to note that there\u2019s no option to selectively delete them. The statistics will reset automatically or when you perform certain actions. Here's how to do it:\n\n1. **Reset All Settings**: This will reset all settings on your iPhone, including network settings, keyboard dictionary, location settings, privacy settings, and Apple Pay cards. It won't delete your data or apps. To do this:\n   - Go to **Settings > General > Transfer or Reset iPhone**.\n   - Tap **Reset**.\n   - Choose **Reset All Settings**.\n   - Enter your passcode if prompted and confirm your choice.\n\n2. **Allow Battery Stats to Reset**: The iPhone auto-updates battery usage statistics based on usage. If you want to clear out the stats and start fresh, you can simply wait for the statistics to reset on their own over time.\n\n3. **Use Low Power Mode**: When you enable Low Power Mode, your battery usage stats may change temporarily based on the features that are being limited.\n\n4. **Restart Your iPhone**: Restarting your device can sometimes refresh various settings, including battery stats.\n\nRemember that while you can reset all settings, this will affect more than just the battery statistics. If you're looking to clear out just the battery statistics without a full reset, unfortunately, that is not possible as of the information available up to October 2023. You can, however, monitor and manage your battery usage through the Settings app under **Settings > Battery**.",
